{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775905864734,"sessionID":"ses_283c33997ffeTKvors8XOn3lV3","part":{"id":"prt_d7c3cee20001U7qrIERA7h1y29","messageID":"msg_d7c3ce0a00013KOOJaksfKxnEI","sessionID":"ses_283c33997ffeTKvors8XOn3lV3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 Design: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Architecture\n4: \n5: ```\n6: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n7: │                    AgentRuntimeClient                        │\n8: │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐       │\n9: │  │ Sync Client  │  │ Async Client │  │  Streaming   │       │\n10: │  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘       │\n11: │         └──────────────────┴──────────────────┘              │\n12: │                            │                                 │\n13: │  ┌─────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────┐       │\n14: │  │              Transport Layer (HTTP/gRPC)           │       │\n15: │  │  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐   │       │\n16: │  │  │  Request   │  │   Retry    │  │  Circuit   │   │       │\n17: │  │  │  Builder   │  │   Logic    │  │  Breaker   │   │       │\n18: │  │  └────────────┘  └────────────┘  └────────────┘   │       │\n19: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘       │\n20: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n21:                               │\n22:                               ▼\n23:                     ┌─────────────────────┐\n24:                     │   AgentRuntime API  │\n25:                     └─────────────────────┘\n26: ```\n27: \n28: ## Design Principles\n29: \n30: 1. **Pythonic API**: Follow Python conventions and best practices\n31: 2. **Type Safety**: Full type hints and Pydantic validation\n32: 3. **Async-First**: Support both sync and async patterns\n33: 4. **Fail-Fast**: Clear exceptions with actionable error messages\n34: 5. **Observability**: Built-in logging and event streaming\n35: \n36: ## Class Design\n37: \n38: ### AgentRuntimeClient\n39: \n40: ```python\n41: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n42:     \"\"\"Client for interacting with the AgentRuntime service.\"\"\"\n43:     \n44:     def __init__(\n45:         self,\n46:         base_url: str,\n47:         api_key: Optional[str] = None,\n48:         timeout: float = 30.0,\n49:         max_retries: int = 3\n50:     ):\n51:         ...\n52:     \n53:     def create_agent(self, config: AgentConfig) -> Agent:\n54:         \"\"\"Create a new agent.\"\"\"\n55:         ...\n56:     \n57:     async def acreate_agent(self, config: AgentConfig) -> Agent:\n58:         \"\"\"Async create a new agent.\"\"\"\n59:         ...\n60: ```\n61: \n62: ### Error Handling Strategy\n63: \n64: - Custom exception hierarchy for different error types\n65: - Automatic retry with exponential backoff for transient errors\n66: - Circuit breaker pattern for cascading failure prevention\n67: \n68: ## Data Flow\n69: \n70: 1. User calls client method with Pydantic model parameters\n71: 2. Request is serialized and validated\n72: 3. Transport layer sends request with retry logic\n73: 4. Response is deserialized into Pydantic models\n74: 5. Result or exception is returned to user\n\n(End of file - total 74 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 Design: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    AgentRuntimeClient                        │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐       │\n│  │ Sync Client  │  │ Async Client │  │  Streaming   │       │\n│  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘       │\n│         └──────────────────┴──────────────────┘              │\n│                            │                                 │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────┐       │\n│  │              Transport Layer (HTTP/gRPC)           │       │\n│  │  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐   │       │\n│  │  │  Request   │  │   Retry    │  │  Circuit   │   │       │\n│  │  │  Builder   │  │   Logic    │  │  Breaker   │   │       │\n│  │  └────────────┘  └────────────┘  └────────────┘   │       │\n│  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘       │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/design.md","time":{"start":1775905864709,"end":1775905864732}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775905864736,"sessionID":"ses_283c33997ffeTKvors8XOn3lV3","part":{"id":"prt_d7c3cf2d3001YcZDGc9kUWbrgd","messageID":"msg_d7c3ce0a00013KOOJaksfKxnEI","sessionID":"ses_283c33997ffeTKvors8XOn3lV3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: AR-028\n2: title: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n3: module: sdk-python\n4: language: Python\n5: size: M\n6: status: open\n7: \n8: # AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n9: # Module: sdk-python\n10: # Language: Python\n11: # Size: M\n12: \n13: # OpenSpec Metadata\n14: openspec:\n15:   version: \"1.0\"\n16:   project: agentcube\n17: \n18: # Architecture Requirement\n19: requirement:\n20:   type: client-sdk\n21:   description: |\n22:     Implement an AgentRuntimeClient class within the sdk-python module to provide\n23:     a Python SDK for interacting with the AgentRuntime service. This client will\n24:     enable developers to programmatically create, manage, and monitor agents\n25:     through a clean, Pythonic API that abstracts the underlying gRPC/HTTP\n26:     communication with the AgentRuntime.\n27: \n28: # Scope\n29: scope:\n30:   in:\n31:     - AgentRuntimeClient class implementation\n32:     - Agent lifecycle management (create, start, stop, delete)\n33:     - Agent configuration and deployment APIs\n34:     - Event streaming and monitoring capabilities\n35:     - Error handling and retry logic\n36:     - Async/sync API support\n37:     - Type hints and pydantic models for all API objects\n38:   out:\n39:     - CLI tool for agent management (separate AR)\n40:     - Authentication/authorization implementation (assumes existing)\n41:     - WebSocket-based real-time updates (separate AR)\n42:     - Multi-region failover handling (separate AR)\n43: \n44: # Acceptance Criteria\n45: acceptance:\n46:   - AgentRuntimeClient provides clean, Pythonic API for all runtime operations\n47:   - Both synchronous and asynchronous APIs are supported\n48:   - Comprehensive type hints for IDE support and type checking\n49:   - Proper error handling with custom exception hierarchy\n50:   - Retry logic with exponential backoff for transient failures\n51:   - Event streaming supports real-time agent status updates\n52:   - Unit and integration test coverage >= 80%\n53:   - Documentation with usage examples\n54: \n55: # References\n56: references:\n57:   - https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n58:   - https://grpc.io/docs/languages/python/\n59:   - https://www.python-httpx.org/\n60: \n61: # Estimation\n62: estimation:\n63:   size: M\n64:   story_points: 5\n65:   days: 3\n\n(End of file - total 65 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: AR-028\ntitle: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\nmodule: sdk-python\nlanguage: Python\nsize: M\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n# Module: sdk-python\n# Language: Python\n# Size: M\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: client-sdk","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775905864713,"end":1775905864734}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775905864738,"sessionID":"ses_283c33997ffeTKvors8XOn3lV3","part":{"id":"prt_d7c3cf74d001V3E62YlyjCfQ9H","messageID":"msg_d7c3ce0a00013KOOJaksfKxnEI","sessionID":"ses_283c33997ffeTKvors8XOn3lV3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/plan.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 Implementation Plan: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Phase 1: Foundation (Day 1)\n4: \n5: ### Tasks\n6: 1. **Setup project structure**\n7:    - Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/` directory\n8:    - Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/` directory\n9:    - Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/exceptions.py`\n10: \n11: 2. **Define data models**\n12:    - Implement `AgentConfig` model\n13:    - Implement `Agent` response model\n14:    - Implement `AgentStatus` model\n15:    - Implement `AgentEvent` model\n16:    - Implement `AgentFilter` model\n17: \n18: 3. **Implement exception hierarchy**\n19:    - Create base `AgentRuntimeError`\n20:    - Create specific exception classes\n21: \n22: ## Phase 2: Core Client (Day 1-2)\n23: \n24: ### Tasks\n25: 1. **Implement base client**\n26:    - Create `BaseClient` with common functionality\n27:    - Implement request/response handling\n28:    - Add logging infrastructure\n29: \n30: 2. **Implement sync client**\n31:    - Create `AgentRuntimeClient` class\n32:    - Implement `create_agent()` method\n33:    - Implement `get_agent()` method\n34:    - Implement `list_agents()` method\n35:    - Implement `start_agent()` method\n36:    - Implement `stop_agent()` method\n37:    - Implement `delete_agent()` method\n38: \n39: 3. **Implement retry logic**\n40:    - Integrate tenacity for retry handling\n41:    - Configure exponential backoff\n42:    - Define retryable vs non-retryable errors\n43: \n44: ## Phase 3: Async Support (Day 2)\n45: \n46: ### Tasks\n47: 1. **Implement async client**\n48:    - Create `AsyncAgentRuntimeClient` class\n49:    - Implement all async variants of sync methods\n50:    - Ensure proper session management\n51: \n52: 2. **Implement event streaming**\n53:    - Create streaming endpoint support\n54:    - Implement `stream_events()` method\n55:    - Handle connection lifecycle\n56: \n57: ## Phase 4: Testing & Documentation (Day 3)\n58: \n59: ### Tasks\n60: 1. **Unit tests**\n61:    - Test all client methods\n62:    - Test retry logic\n63:    - Test error handling\n64:    - Mock transport layer\n65: \n66: 2. **Integration tests**\n67:    - Test against mock server\n68:    - Verify serialization/deserialization\n69:    - Test streaming functionality\n70: \n71: 3. **Documentation**\n72:    - Add docstrings to all public APIs\n73:    - Create usage examples\n74:    - Write README section\n75: \n76: ## Dependencies\n77: \n78: ```\n79: sdk-python/\n80: ├── src/agentcube/\n81: │   ├── __init__.py\n82: │   ├── client/\n83: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n84: │   │   ├── runtime_client.py\n85: │   │   ├── async_client.py\n86: │   │   └── retry.py\n87: │   ├── models/\n88: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n89: │   │   ├── config.py\n90: │   │   └── responses.py\n91: │   └── exceptions.py\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ## Risk Mitigation\n95: \n96: - Use established libraries (httpx, pydantic, tenacity)\n97: - Follow existing project patterns from other SDKs\n98: - Regular testing during development\n\n(End of file - total 98 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 Implementation Plan: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Phase 1: Foundation (Day 1)\n\n### Tasks\n1. **Setup project structure**\n   - Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/` directory\n   - Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/` directory\n   - Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/exceptions.py`\n\n2. **Define data models**\n   - Implement `AgentConfig` model\n   - Implement `Agent` response model\n   - Implement `AgentStatus` model\n   - Implement `AgentEvent` model\n   - Implement `AgentFilter` model\n\n3. **Implement exception hierarchy**\n   - Create base `AgentRuntimeError`\n   - Create specific exception classes","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/plan.md","time":{"start":1775905864715,"end":1775905864736}}}}
