{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775905880052,"sessionID":"ses_283c33997ffeTKvors8XOn3lV3","part":{"id":"prt_d7c3d2ecf001v6calT68l7J48I","messageID":"msg_d7c3d189e001xhTT23TkwZpmL7","sessionID":"ses_283c33997ffeTKvors8XOn3lV3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 Delta Specification: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document specifies the delta changes required to implement the AgentRuntimeClient SDK for Python.\n6: \n7: ## New Components\n8: \n9: ### 1. AgentRuntimeClient Class\n10: \n11: **Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/runtime_client.py`\n12: \n13: **Description:** Main client class for interacting with the AgentRuntime service.\n14: \n15: **Key Methods:**\n16: - `create_agent(config: AgentConfig) -> Agent`\n17: - `start_agent(agent_id: str) -> AgentStatus`\n18: - `stop_agent(agent_id: str) -> AgentStatus`\n19: - `delete_agent(agent_id: str) -> None`\n20: - `get_agent(agent_id: str) -> Agent`\n21: - `list_agents(filters: AgentFilter) -> List[Agent]`\n22: - `stream_events(agent_id: str) -> Iterator[AgentEvent]`\n23: \n24: ### 2. Configuration Models\n25: \n26: **Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/config.py`\n27: \n28: **Description:** Pydantic models for agent configuration.\n29: \n30: **Classes:**\n31: - `AgentConfig`\n32: - `AgentResources`\n33: - `AgentEnvironment`\n34: \n35: ### 3. Response Models\n36: \n37: **Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/responses.py`\n38: \n39: **Description:** Pydantic models for API responses.\n40: \n41: **Classes:**\n42: - `Agent`\n43: - `AgentStatus`\n44: - `AgentEvent`\n45: - `AgentFilter`\n46: \n47: ### 4. Exception Hierarchy\n48: \n49: **Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/exceptions.py`\n50: \n51: **Description:** Custom exceptions for error handling.\n52: \n53: **Classes:**\n54: - `AgentRuntimeError` (base)\n55: - `AgentNotFoundError`\n56: - `AgentCreationError`\n57: - `ConnectionError`\n58: - `AuthenticationError`\n59: \n60: ### 5. Retry Logic\n61: \n62: **Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/retry.py`\n63: \n64: **Description:** Retry decorator and utilities.\n65: \n66: ## Modified Components\n67: \n68: None - this is a new feature implementation.\n69: \n70: ## Interface Contracts\n71: \n72: ### gRPC/HTTP Endpoints\n73: \n74: The client will communicate with the following endpoints:\n75: \n76: - `POST /v1/agents` - Create agent\n77: - `GET /v1/agents/{id}` - Get agent\n78: - `DELETE /v1/agents/{id}` - Delete agent\n79: - `POST /v1/agents/{id}/start` - Start agent\n80: - `POST /v1/agents/{id}/stop` - Stop agent\n81: - `GET /v1/agents` - List agents\n82: - `GET /v1/agents/{id}/events` - Stream events\n83: \n84: ## Dependencies\n85: \n86: - `httpx` or `aiohttp` for HTTP client\n87: - `pydantic` for data validation\n88: - `tenacity` for retry logic\n\n(End of file - total 88 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 Delta Specification: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document specifies the delta changes required to implement the AgentRuntimeClient SDK for Python.\n\n## New Components\n\n### 1. AgentRuntimeClient Class\n\n**Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/runtime_client.py`\n\n**Description:** Main client class for interacting with the AgentRuntime service.\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `create_agent(config: AgentConfig) -> Agent`\n- `start_agent(agent_id: str) -> AgentStatus`\n- `stop_agent(agent_id: str) -> AgentStatus`\n- `delete_agent(agent_id: str) -> None`\n- `get_agent(agent_id: str) -> Agent`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775905880037,"end":1775905880051}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775905880056,"sessionID":"ses_283c33997ffeTKvors8XOn3lV3","part":{"id":"prt_d7c3d3362001CjfgHBejcU10ib","messageID":"msg_d7c3d189e001xhTT23TkwZpmL7","sessionID":"ses_283c33997ffeTKvors8XOn3lV3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/notes.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/notes.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 Notes: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Created\n4: Date: 2026-04-11\n5: \n6: ## Context\n7: \n8: This change implements the Python SDK client for the AgentRuntime service. The client will provide both synchronous and asynchronous APIs for managing agent lifecycle, configuration, and monitoring.\n9: \n10: ## Design Decisions\n11: \n12: ### HTTP vs gRPC\n13: Initially considering HTTP/REST for broader compatibility, but gRPC may be evaluated if performance becomes critical.\n14: \n15: ### Library Choices\n16: - **HTTP Client**: `httpx` - supports both sync and async, modern API\n17: - **Validation**: `pydantic` - already used in project, excellent type support\n18: - **Retry**: `tenacity` - battle-tested, flexible retry strategies\n19: \n20: ## Open Questions\n21: \n22: 1. What is the exact API endpoint structure for the AgentRuntime service?\n23: 2. Are there existing API specifications (OpenAPI/Swagger) to reference?\n24: 3. What authentication mechanism should the client support?\n25: 4. Should we support connection pooling for high-throughput scenarios?\n26: \n27: ## References\n28: \n29: - Project: agentcube\n30: - Module: sdk-python\n31: - Language: Python 3.9+\n\n(End of file - total 31 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 Notes: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Created\nDate: 2026-04-11\n\n## Context\n\nThis change implements the Python SDK client for the AgentRuntime service. The client will provide both synchronous and asynchronous APIs for managing agent lifecycle, configuration, and monitoring.\n\n## Design Decisions\n\n### HTTP vs gRPC\nInitially considering HTTP/REST for broader compatibility, but gRPC may be evaluated if performance becomes critical.\n\n### Library Choices\n- **HTTP Client**: `httpx` - supports both sync and async, modern API\n- **Validation**: `pydantic` - already used in project, excellent type support\n- **Retry**: `tenacity` - battle-tested, flexible retry strategies\n\n## Open Questions","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/notes.md","time":{"start":1775905880040,"end":1775905880053}}}}
