{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775906078318,"sessionID":"ses_283c33997ffeTKvors8XOn3lV3","part":{"id":"prt_d7c3d6586001PWs037YRyDEGJq","messageID":"msg_d7c3d38280016zlg0i3VhI53a7","sessionID":"ses_283c33997ffeTKvors8XOn3lV3","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md","content":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-028\n> **Module:** `sdk-python`\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement an `AgentRuntimeClient` class within the `sdk-python` module to provide a Python SDK for interacting with the AgentRuntime service. This client enables developers to programmatically create, manage, and monitor agents through a clean, Pythonic API with both synchronous and asynchronous support.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.1 — Project Structure Setup\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.1.1 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/` directory | Directory exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.1.2 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/` directory | Directory exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.1.3 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/exceptions.py` | File exists with module docstring | 0.1h |\n| 3.1.4 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/__init__.py` | Exports main client classes | 0.1h |\n| 3.1.5 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/__init__.py` | Exports all model classes | 0.1h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Project structure ready for implementation.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.2 — Data Model Definitions (Config)\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.2.1 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/config.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.2.2 | Implement `AgentConfig` Pydantic model | Model with name, image, env vars fields | 0.5h |\n| 3.2.3 | Implement `AgentResources` Pydantic model | CPU, memory, GPU fields with validators | 0.5h |\n| 3.2.4 | Implement `AgentEnvironment` Pydantic model | Environment variables dict with validation | 0.5h |\n| 3.2.5 | Add `AgentConfig` validators (required fields, format) | Invalid configs raise ValidationError | 0.5h |\n| 3.2.6 | Add JSON schema export for `AgentConfig` | `.model_json_schema()` works | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Config models defined with validation.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.3 — Data Model Definitions (Responses)\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.3.1 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/responses.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.3.2 | Implement `AgentStatus` Enum | PENDING, RUNNING, STOPPED, ERROR states | 0.25h |\n| 3.3.3 | Implement `Agent` Pydantic model | id, name, status, config, created_at fields | 0.5h |\n| 3.3.4 | Implement `AgentEvent` Pydantic model | timestamp, type, payload fields | 0.5h |\n| 3.3.5 | Implement `AgentFilter` Pydantic model | status, name_pattern, tags fields | 0.5h |\n| 3.3.6 | Add response model validators | Datetime parsing, enum validation | 0.25h |\n| 3.3.7 | Export all models from `models/__init__.py` | `from agentcube.models import AgentConfig, Agent` works | 0.1h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Response models defined with validation.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.4 — Exception Hierarchy\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.4.1 | Implement `AgentRuntimeError` base exception | Base class with message, code attrs | 0.25h |\n| 3.4.2 | Implement `AgentNotFoundError` (404) | Raised when agent ID not found | 0.25h |\n| 3.4.3 | Implement `AgentCreationError` (400/422) | Raised when creation fails | 0.25h |\n| 3.4.4 | Implement `ConnectionError` (network) | Raised on transport failures | 0.25h |\n| 3.4.5 | Implement `AuthenticationError` (401/403) | Raised on auth failures | 0.25h |\n| 3.4.6 | Implement `ValidationError` (400) | Raised on request validation failures | 0.25h |\n| 3.4.7 | Export all exceptions from `exceptions.py` | `from agentcube.exceptions import AgentRuntimeError` works | 0.1h |\n| 3.4.8 | Add HTTP status code mapping | Each exception has `.status_code` property | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Exception hierarchy defined and exportable.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.5 — Base Client Foundation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.5.1 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/base.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.5.2 | Implement `BaseClient.__init__()` with base_url, api_key, timeout | Attributes stored correctly | 0.5h |\n| 3.5.3 | Implement `_build_url()` method | URL construction works for endpoints | 0.25h |\n| 3.5.4 | Implement `_build_headers()` method | Auth header included when api_key set | 0.25h |\n| 3.5.5 | Add logging infrastructure | Logger created with module name | 0.25h |\n| 3.5.6 | Implement `_handle_response_error()` method | Maps HTTP errors to exceptions | 0.5h |\n| 3.5.7 | Add request/response serialization helpers | JSON encoding/decoding works | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Base client with common functionality.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.6 — Sync Client Implementation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.6.1 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/runtime_client.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.6.2 | Implement `AgentRuntimeClient` class extending BaseClient | Class defined with proper inheritance | 0.25h |\n| 3.6.3 | Implement `create_agent(config) -> Agent` method | Returns Agent on success, raises on failure | 0.5h |\n| 3.6.4 | Implement `get_agent(agent_id) -> Agent` method | Returns Agent or raises AgentNotFoundError | 0.5h |\n| 3.6.5 | Implement `list_agents(filters) -> List[Agent]` method | Returns list, handles pagination | 0.5h |\n| 3.6.6 | Implement `start_agent(agent_id) -> AgentStatus` method | Returns new status | 0.5h |\n| 3.6.7 | Implement `stop_agent(agent_id) -> AgentStatus` method | Returns new status | 0.5h |\n| 3.6.8 | Implement `delete_agent(agent_id) -> None` method | Returns None on success | 0.5h |\n| 3.6.9 | Export `AgentRuntimeClient` from `client/__init__.py` | Import works from agentcube.client | 0.1h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Sync client with all CRUD operations.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.7 — Retry Logic Implementation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.7.1 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/retry.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.7.2 | Define retry configuration dataclass | max_retries, backoff_factor, max_wait | 0.25h |\n| 3.7.3 | Implement retry decorator with tenacity | Decorator applies to methods | 0.5h |\n| 3.7.4 | Configure exponential backoff strategy | Wait time increases exponentially | 0.25h |\n| 3.7.5 | Define retryable exceptions (ConnectionError, 5xx) | Retries on transient errors only | 0.25h |\n| 3.7.6 | Define non-retryable exceptions (4xx except 429) | No retry on client errors | 0.25h |\n| 3.7.7 | Add retry logging | Logs retry attempts with level INFO | 0.25h |\n| 3.7.8 | Apply retry decorator to sync client methods | All API calls have retry | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Retry logic integrated with client.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.8 — Async Client Implementation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.8.1 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/async_client.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.8.2 | Implement `AsyncAgentRuntimeClient` class | Class defined with async methods | 0.25h |\n| 3.8.3 | Implement `__init__()` with httpx.AsyncClient | Async client initialized | 0.25h |\n| 3.8.4 | Implement `acreate_agent()` method | Async create works | 0.5h |\n| 3.8.5 | Implement `aget_agent()` method | Async get works | 0.5h |\n| 3.8.6 | Implement `alist_agents()` method | Async list works | 0.5h |\n| 3.8.7 | Implement `astart_agent()` method | Async start works | 0.5h |\n| 3.8.8 | Implement `astop_agent()` method | Async stop works | 0.5h |\n| 3.8.9 | Implement `adelete_agent()` method | Async delete works | 0.5h |\n| 3.8.10 | Apply retry decorator to async methods | Async retries work | 0.25h |\n| 3.8.11 | Export `AsyncAgentRuntimeClient` from `client/__init__.py` | Import works | 0.1h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Async client with all operations.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.9 — Event Streaming\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.9.1 | Implement `stream_events(agent_id)` in sync client | Returns Iterator[AgentEvent] | 0.5h |\n| 3.9.2 | Implement `astream_events(agent_id)` in async client | Returns AsyncIterator[AgentEvent] | 0.5h |\n| 3.9.3 | Handle SSE (Server-Sent Events) parsing | Events parsed correctly | 0.5h |\n| 3.9.4 | Handle connection lifecycle (open, close, error) | Proper cleanup on disconnect | 0.5h |\n| 3.9.5 | Add stream reconnection on transient errors | Reconnects with backoff | 0.5h |\n| 3.9.6 | Add stream timeout handling | Raises ConnectionError on timeout | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Event streaming functional.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.10 — Unit Tests — Models\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.10.1 | Create `sdk-python/tests/unit/test_models_config.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.10.2 | Write `TestAgentConfig` — valid data passes | All required fields accepted | 0.5h |\n| 3.10.3 | Write `TestAgentConfig` — invalid data rejected | ValidationError raised | 0.5h |\n| 3.10.4 | Write `TestAgentResources` — resource limits | CPU/memory validation | 0.5h |\n| 3.10.5 | Create `sdk-python/tests/unit/test_models_responses.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.10.6 | Write `TestAgentResponse` — parsing | JSON parses to Agent model | 0.5h |\n| 3.10.7 | Write `TestAgentStatus` — enum values | All status values valid | 0.25h |\n| 3.10.8 | Write `TestAgentEvent` — event parsing | Event stream parsing works | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Model unit tests pass.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.11 — Unit Tests — Sync Client\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.11.1 | Create `sdk-python/tests/unit/test_runtime_client.py` | File exists with fixtures | 0.25h |\n| 3.11.2 | Write `TestAgentRuntimeClientInit` — initialization | Client creates with config | 0.5h |\n| 3.11.3 | Write `TestCreateAgent` — success case | Returns Agent, POST called | 0.5h |\n| 3.11.4 | Write `TestCreateAgent` — error case | Raises AgentCreationError | 0.5h |\n| 3.11.5 | Write `TestGetAgent` — found and not found | Returns Agent or raises | 0.5h |\n| 3.11.6 | Write `TestListAgents` — with and without filters | Returns list | 0.5h |\n| 3.11.7 | Write `TestStartStopAgent` — status changes | Returns updated status | 0.5h |\n| 3.11.8 | Write `TestDeleteAgent` — success case | DELETE called, no error | 0.5h |\n| 3.11.9 | Mock transport layer with responses library | HTTP calls mocked | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Sync client tests pass.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.12 — Unit Tests — Async Client\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.12.1 | Create `sdk-python/tests/unit/test_async_client.py` | File exists with async fixtures | 0.25h |\n| 3.12.2 | Write `TestAsyncClientInit` — async initialization | AsyncClient creates | 0.5h |\n| 3.12.3 | Write `TestAsyncCreateAgent` — async CRUD | All async methods tested | 1.0h |\n| 3.12.4 | Write `TestAsyncConcurrent` — concurrent operations | Multiple agents handled | 0.5h |\n| 3.12.5 | Mock async transport with respx/httpx | Async HTTP mocked | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Async client tests pass.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.13 — Unit Tests — Retry Logic\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.13.1 | Create `sdk-python/tests/unit/test_retry.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.13.2 | Write `TestRetrySuccess` — succeeds after retry | Eventually passes | 0.5h |\n| 3.13.3 | Write `TestRetryExhausted` — fails after max | Raises after retries | 0.5h |\n| 3.13.4 | Write `TestRetryableErrors` — retries on 5xx | Retries on server errors | 0.5h |\n| 3.13.5 | Write `TestNonRetryableErrors` — no retry on 4xx | No retry on client errors | 0.5h |\n| 3.13.6 | Write `TestExponentialBackoff` — wait times | Increasing delays verified | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Retry logic tests pass.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.14 — Unit Tests — Exceptions\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.14.1 | Create `sdk-python/tests/unit/test_exceptions.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.14.2 | Write `TestExceptionHierarchy` — inheritance | All extend AgentRuntimeError | 0.25h |\n| 3.14.3 | Write `TestExceptionProperties` — status codes | Correct codes on exceptions | 0.25h |\n| 3.14.4 | Write `TestExceptionMessages` — error messages | Messages formatted correctly | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Exception tests pass.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.15 — Integration Tests\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.15.1 | Create `sdk-python/tests/integration/test_client_integration.py` | File with fixtures | 0.25h |\n| 3.15.2 | Test full CRUD lifecycle | Create → Get → Update → Delete | 1.0h |\n| 3.15.3 | Test against mock server (pytest-httpx) | Mock responses configured | 0.5h |\n| 3.15.4 | Test streaming with mock SSE | Events streamed correctly | 0.5h |\n| 3.15.5 | Test error scenarios (timeouts, 5xx) | Errors handled gracefully | 0.5h |\n| 3.15.6 | Test async full lifecycle | Async CRUD works end-to-end | 1.0h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Integration tests pass.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.16 — Documentation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.16.1 | Add module docstrings to all files | pydoc shows overview | 0.5h |\n| 3.16.2 | Add class docstrings to AgentRuntimeClient | Description and usage | 0.25h |\n| 3.16.3 | Add class docstrings to AsyncAgentRuntimeClient | Async usage documented | 0.25h |\n| 3.16.4 | Add docstrings to all public methods | Args, returns, raises documented | 0.5h |\n| 3.16.5 | Add type hints to all signatures | mypy passes without errors | 0.5h |\n| 3.16.6 | Create usage examples in docstrings | Example code in docstrings | 0.5h |\n| 3.16.7 | Update SDK README with client usage | README shows basic usage | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Documentation complete.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.17 — Lint & Type Check\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.17.1 | Run `ruff check` on sdk-python files | No lint errors | 0.25h |\n| 3.17.2 | Run `mypy` on sdk-python files | No type errors | 0.25h |\n| 3.17.3 | Fix any ruff issues | All checks pass | 0.5h |\n| 3.17.4 | Fix any mypy issues | All checks pass | 0.5h |\n| 3.17.5 | Run `ruff format` for consistent style | Files formatted | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Code passes all checks.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.18 — Package Integration\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.18.1 | Update `pyproject.toml` with new dependencies | httpx, tenacity, pydantic listed | 0.25h |\n| 3.18.2 | Verify package installs with `pip install -e \".[dev]\"` | Installation succeeds | 0.25h |\n| 3.18.3 | Verify imports work from installed package | `from agentcube.client import AgentRuntimeClient` works | 0.25h |\n| 3.18.4 | Update `sdk-python/README.md` with quickstart | Quickstart section added | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Package fully integrated.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Phase | Tasks | Est. Hours |\n|-------|-------|------------|\n| ST-3.1: Project Structure | 5 | 0.5h |\n| ST-3.2: Config Models | 6 | 2.0h |\n| ST-3.3: Response Models | 7 | 2.2h |\n| ST-3.4: Exceptions | 8 | 2.0h |\n| ST-3.5: Base Client | 7 | 2.3h |\n| ST-3.6: Sync Client | 9 | 3.6h |\n| ST-3.7: Retry Logic | 8 | 2.1h |\n| ST-3.8: Async Client | 11 | 4.4h |\n| ST-3.9: Event Streaming | 6 | 2.8h |\n| ST-3.10: Unit Tests — Models | 8 | 3.4h |\n| ST-3.11: Unit Tests — Sync | 9 | 4.3h |\n| ST-3.12: Unit Tests — Async | 5 | 2.8h |\n| ST-3.13: Unit Tests — Retry | 6 | 2.6h |\n| ST-3.14: Unit Tests — Exceptions | 4 | 0.9h |\n| ST-3.15: Integration Tests | 6 | 3.8h |\n| ST-3.16: Documentation | 7 | 3.0h |\n| ST-3.17: Lint & Type Check | 5 | 1.8h |\n| ST-3.18: Package Integration | 4 | 1.3h |\n| **Total** | **121** | **45.0h** |\n\n---\n\n## File Deliverables Checklist\n\n- [ ] `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/config.py` — Configuration models\n- [ ] `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/responses.py` — Response models\n- [ ] `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/__init__.py` — Model exports\n- [ ] `sdk-python/src/agentcube/exceptions.py` — Exception hierarchy\n- [ ] `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/base.py` — Base client\n- [ ] `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/runtime_client.py` — Sync client\n- [ ] `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/async_client.py` — Async client\n- [ ] `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/retry.py` — Retry logic\n- [ ] `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/__init__.py` — Client exports\n- [ ] `sdk-python/tests/unit/test_models_config.py` — Config model tests\n- [ ] `sdk-python/tests/unit/test_models_responses.py` — Response model tests\n- [ ] `sdk-python/tests/unit/test_runtime_client.py` — Sync client tests\n- [ ] `sdk-python/tests/unit/test_async_client.py` — Async client tests\n- [ ] `sdk-python/tests/unit/test_retry.py` — Retry tests\n- [ ] `sdk-python/tests/unit/test_exceptions.py` — Exception tests\n- [ ] `sdk-python/tests/integration/test_client_integration.py` — Integration tests\n\n---\n\n## Verification Commands\n\n```bash\n# Install verification\npip install -e \"sdk-python/[dev,test]\"\n\n# Import verification\npython -c \"from agentcube.client import AgentRuntimeClient, AsyncAgentRuntimeClient\"\npython -c \"from agentcube.models import AgentConfig, Agent, AgentStatus\"\npython -c \"from agentcube.exceptions import AgentRuntimeError, AgentNotFoundError\"\n\n# Unit test verification\npytest sdk-python/tests/unit/ -v\n\n# Integration tests\npytest sdk-python/tests/integration/ -v\n\n# Coverage report\npytest --cov=agentcube.client --cov=agentcube.models --cov-report=term-missing\n\n# Lint verification\nruff check sdk-python/src/agentcube/\nmypy sdk-python/src/agentcube/\n```\n\n---\n\n## Definition of Done\n\n- [ ] All 121 tasks complete\n- [ ] Package installs successfully (`pip install -e sdk-python/`)\n- [ ] AgentRuntimeClient importable from `agentcube.client`\n- [ ] AsyncAgentRuntimeClient importable from `agentcube.client`\n- [ ] All unit tests pass (>80% coverage)\n- [ ] All integration tests pass\n- [ ] Type checking passes (`mypy`)\n- [ ] Linting passes (`ruff`)\n- [ ] Documentation complete with docstrings\n- [ ] Usage examples in README\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `httpx>=0.25.0` — HTTP client (sync + async)\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0` — Data validation (already in pyproject.toml)\n- `tenacity>=8.2.0` — Retry logic\n- `pytest>=7.4.0` — Testing framework (already present)\n- `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0` — Async test support\n- `pytest-httpx>=0.22.0` — HTTP mocking for tests\n- `respx>=0.20.0` — HTTPX mocking (optional alternative)\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- Follow existing code style in sdk-python\n- Ensure type hints on all public methods\n- Use `httpx` for both sync and async HTTP (unified API)\n- Keep models immutable where possible (frozen=True)\n- Document all raised exceptions in docstrings\n\n---\n\n*AR-028 — Module: sdk-python — Language: Python — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775906078276,"end":1775906078314}}}}
